_meanings:
{@--1@} To arise, proceed,
spring up, to be born or produced,
originate (with <ab>abl.</ab>); {#loBAt kroDaH#}
{#praBavati#} <ls>H. 1. 27</ls>; {#svAyaMBuvAnmarIceryaH#} 
{#prabaBUva prajApatiH#} <ls>Ś. 7. 9</ls>; {#puruzaH#} 
{#prabaBUvAgnervismayena sahartvijAM#} <ls>R. 10. 50</ls>;  
<ls>Bg. 8. 18.</ls>

{@--4@} To be strong
or powerful, prevail, predominate,
show one's power; {#praBavati hi mahimnA#}
{#svena yogISvarIyaM#} <ls>Māl. 9. 52</ls>; {#praBavati#}
{#BagabAn viDiH#} <ls>K.</ls>; <ls>Pt. 1. 44.</ls>

{@--5@} To
be able or equal, have power for
(with <ab>inf.</ab>); {#kusumAnyapi#} 
{#gAtrasaMgamAtpraBavaMtyAyurapohituM yadi#} <ls>R. 8. 44</ls>;  
{#konyo hutavahAddagDuM praBavizyati#} <ls>Ś. 4</ls>;  
<ls>Ś. 6. 30</ls>; <ls>V. 1. 9</ls>; <ls>U. 2. 4</ls>; <ls>Pt. 1.</ls>

{@--6@} To have control or power over,
prevail over, be master of (usually
with <ab>gen.</ab>, sometimes with <ab>dat.</ab> or
<ab>loc.</ab>); {#yadi praBavizyAmyAtmanaH#} <ls>Ś. 1</ls>;  
{#praBavati nijasya kanyakAjanasya mahArAjaH#}
<ls>Māl. 4</ls>; {#tatpraBavati anuSAsane devI#} <ls>Ve. 2</ls>;
{#viDirapi na yeByaH praBavati#} <ls>Bh. 2. 94.</ls>

{@--8@} To be
sufficient for, be able to contain;
<ls>Ku. 6. 59.</ls>

{@--9@} To be contained in
(wit <ab>loc.</ab>); {#guruH praharzaH prabaBUva#} 
{#nAtmani#} <ls>R. 3. 17.</ls>
